[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = LineBroadenings","category":"page"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for LineBroadenings.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [LineBroadenings]","category":"page"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings.Gaussian","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings.Gaussian","text":"Gaussian(μ, σ)\n\nGaussian distribution, also called normal distribution.\n\nDefinition\n\nfleft(x  mu sigmaright)=frac1sigma sqrt2 pi expleft-frac12\nleft(fracx-musigmaright)^2right\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: mean or expectation\nσ::Real: standard deviation\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings.Lorentz","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings.Lorentz","text":"Lorentz(μ, γ)\n\nLorentz distribution, also called Cauchy distribution.\n\nfleft(x  mu gammaright)=frac1pi gammaleft1+left(fracx-mu\ngammaright)^2right=frac1pi gammaleftfracgamma^2\nleft(x-muright)^2+gamma^2right\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: location parameter\nγ::Real: scale parameter\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings.Voigt","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings.Voigt","text":"Voigt(μ, σ, γ)\n\nThe Voigt profile is a probability distribution given by a convolution of a Cauchy-Lorentz distribution and a Gaussian distribution.\n\nDefinition\n\nf(x mu sigma gamma) equiv G(xmu sigma) otimes L(xmu gamma)\n\nIt can be evaluated as\n\nf(x mu sigma gamma)=fracoperatornameRew(z)sigma sqrt2 pi\n\nwhere mathrmRew(z) is the real part of the Faddeeva function evaluated for\n\nz=fracx-mu+i gammasigma sqrt2\n\nFields\n\nμ::Real: location parameter\nσ::Real: σ in Gaussian distribution\nγ::Real: γ in Lorentz distribution\n\nExternal links\n\nWikipedia\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#LineBroadenings.pdf","page":"Home","title":"LineBroadenings.pdf","text":"pdf(d::Profile, x::Real)\n\nprobability density function\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
